Date:2/16/2011 5:30:03 PM
From:MCsweet
I'm fine with volatility in net-net and microcap type situations where market
prices bounce around much more than any change in underlying company
fundamentals. As long as the basic business remains sound, I have few worries.
Price volatility leads to great trading opportunities , and if prices go down,
I am happy buying more.

However, stocks that are heavily dependent on macro factors (such as miners)
tend to result in some heartburn for me. A company's prospects can go from
great to poor depending on the global factors beyond my control/understanding.
This is especially true if the company has a lot of debt. I am usually not
inclined to step up for large positions in those cases.

MC
